<h1> Muffin Recipe</h1> A basic recipe. 
You can add pretty much anything to it!
<h2> Ingrdients </h2>
<ul>
<li> 2 eggs </li>
<li> 200g caster sugar 4 </li>
<li> 250ml milk </li>
<li> 125ml vegetable oil </li>
<li> 400g plain flour </li>
<li> 3tbsp baking powder </li>
<li> 1tbsp salt </li>
</ul>
<h2> Method </h2>
<ol>
<li> Preheat oven to Gas Mark 6 or a medium temperature. Line muffin tray with paper muffin cases. </li>
<li> Beat the eggs in a mixing bowl and then mix in the oil and milk. Add the sugar and whisk until desolved. </li>
<li> Sift in the dry ingredients: flour, baking powder and salt and mix until smooth. NB: add any extra ingredients now eg. chocolate chip/fruit. </li>
<li> Fill muffin cases TWO THIRDS full (this is important for the perfect size muffins) and bake in the middle of the oven for 25 min (approx.) </li>
<li> Leave to cool (or enjoy warm!) </li>
</ol>
